The paper focuses on the impact of affective states on software developers' performance, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of human factors in software development, which could also be categorized under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The study involves programming tasks, which could be classified under programming languages (cs.PL) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper introduces a measurement instrument and a linear mixed-effects model, which could be categorized under signal processing (cs.SI).
